8. Market Definition

Proposed neutral definition



GTM Engineer (Go‑to‑Market Engineer) – a technical professional who designs, builds, and operates the data‑driven, automated infrastructure that enables a company’s revenue‑generation motions (acquisition, conversion, expansion, and post‑sale). The role blends software‑engineering practices (API development, cloud functions, code‑level automation) with revenue‑operations knowledge (CRM, lead routing, pipeline analytics) and increasingly leverages generative‑AI / LLM agents to augment or replace manual sales/marketing workflows. GTM Engineers are expected to partner closely with sales, marketing, customer‑success, product, and engineering stakeholders to translate business problems into production‑grade solutions, measure impact on pipeline/revenue, and iterate rapidly.



