9. Open Questions and Data Limitations


Missing salary/compensation data – the sample provides no consistent pay bands; understanding market pricing would require compensation benchmarks.

Full job posting context – trimmed descriptions omit many details (e.g., team size, reporting line, performance metrics) that could refine archetype boundaries.

Geographic distribution bias – the sample is heavily weighted toward US‑based roles; it does not capture possible GTM Engineering practices in Europe, APAC, or LATAM.

Temporal dynamics – all postings are from a single snapshot; trends (e.g., rapid rise of LLM‑agent work) may be accelerating and are not captured longitudinally.

Skill‑assessment rigor – we cannot determine how rigorously companies test for AI‑agent expertise versus low‑code familiarity.


Further data that would improve confidence:



